      },
      {
        "ad": "Ted Lemon",
        "end": "2014-10-16 07:40:52-07:00",
        "end_reason": "position_updated",
        "start": "2014-10-16 06:07:50-07:00",
        "text": "This has probably already been considered and addressed by the working group, but coming into this as a neophyte it seems like a glaring omission that the security considerations of bearer assertions are not discussed here.\u00a0  Isn't it the case that the use of bearer assertions requires a trust relationship between the client and relying party such that the client can be assured that the relying party will not misuse the assertion to authenticate with some other entity?\u00a0  I realize that this sort of assertion will likely only be used in cases where the assertion only works to authenticate to a specific relying party, but I think this bears mentioning in the security considerations.",
        "type": "Discuss"
      },
